ai_enrichment.traditional_solution:
To solve this, we must ensure all units match. We convert the speed from km/hr to m/sec by multiplying by $\frac{5}{18}$:

$$
20\times\frac{5}{18}
=
\frac{50}{9}
$$

So, the speed is $\frac{50}{9}$ m/sec. Next, we find the time taken in seconds using the formula $\text{Time} = \frac{\text{Distance}}{\text{Speed}}$:

$$
400\div\frac{50}{9}
=
400\times\frac{9}{50}
=
72
$$

This gives $72$ seconds. Finally, we convert seconds to minutes by dividing by $60$:

$$
\frac{72}{60}
=
\frac{6}{5}
=
1\frac{1}{5}
$$

Thus, the time taken is $1\frac{1}{5}$ min.

